<p>I am converting string to byte using <code>Encoding.Unicode.GetBytes()</code> but it always add an additional <code>zero</code>. here my code is</p>  <pre><code>Dim StringBytes As Byte() = Encoding.Unicode.GetBytes("s") </code></pre>  <p>gives result as </p>  <pre><code>115 0 </code></pre>  <p>Another example:</p>  <pre><code>Dim StringBytes As Byte() = Encoding.Unicode.GetBytes("mm") </code></pre>  <p>gives result as </p>  <pre><code>109 0 109 0 </code></pre>  <p>Why this zero is always added?</p>